<subSubSection id="80A1656BFFDD0E6CFF6D069AFC52F8B5" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C80436E0FFDD0E6CFF6D069AFC52F8B5" blockId="2.[136,1452,1664,2087]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFF6D069AFE50F905" bold="true" box="[189,395,1664,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Risk assessment:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDD0E6CFE77069BFDC5F904" authorityName="Baldesi &amp; Vollesen" authorityYear="2022" box="[423,542,1664,1691]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eilensis">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFE77069BFE63F904" box="[423,440,1665,1690]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFE1A069AFDC5F904" box="[458,542,1664,1690]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">eilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="17008842FFDD0E6CFC99069BFCA2F905" box="[841,889,1665,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
locality. No information was recorded about its abundance at the 
<typeStatus id="17008842FFDD0E6CFE9B06BFFEA0F921" box="[331,379,1701,1727]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
locality. Due to the present political situation in this part of 
<collectingCountry id="B0AC7670FFDD0E6CFBCD06BEFBA2F920" box="[1053,1145,1700,1726]" name="Somalia" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Somalia</collectingCountry>
it has also been impossible to gather any 
<typeStatus id="17008842FFDD0E6CFECF06D2FE16F97C" box="[287,461,1736,1762]" isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">further material</typeStatus>
or any information about the present conditions of the vegetation in the 
<location id="CD64603BFFDD0E6CFB3E06D2FA95F97D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:401287F6FFDE0E6DFF5802EDFAC3F9AA:CD64603BFFDD0E6CFB3E06D2FA95F97D" box="[1262,1358,1736,1763]" country="Somalia" county="Data Deficient" municipality="In" name="Eyl area" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Eyl area</location>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="2860AC9AFFDD0E6CFA8706D3FAB5F97D" box="[1367,1390,1737,1763]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">In</collectingMunicipality>
view of the absence of any data about the status of its habitat and the nature and extent of threats (
<bibRefCitation id="AC2A4B11FFDD0E6CFB7506F6FA44F899" author="Ullah, S. &amp; Gadain, H." box="[1189,1439,1772,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" refId="ref4120" refString="Ullah, S. &amp; Gadain, H. (2016) National Biodiversity Strategy and Action Plan (NBSAP) of Somalia. FAO-Somalia, 164 pp." type="book" year="2016">Ullah &amp; Gadain 2016</bibRefCitation>
), this species has to be assessed as 
<collectingCounty id="21654E6CFFDD0E6CFE2E070BFD79F8B4" box="[510,674,1808,1835]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Data Deficient</collectingCounty>
(DD) (
<bibRefCitation id="AC2A4B11FFDD0E6CFD23070BFCA6F8B5" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[755,893,1809,1835]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" refId="ref3295" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2019) G uidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13. Available from: [http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf]" type="url" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="80A1656BFFDD0E6DFF6D072EFAC3F9AA" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C80436E0FFDD0E6CFF6D072EFBF4F825" blockId="2.[136,1452,1664,2087]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFF6D072EFEEEF8D0" bold="true" box="[189,309,1844,1870]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Affinities:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDD0E6CFE81072EFDC2F8D0" authorityName="Baldesi &amp; Vollesen" authorityYear="2022" box="[337,537,1844,1870]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eilensis">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFE81072EFDC2F8D0" box="[337,537,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Blepharis eilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDD0E6CFD7A072FFCE5F8D1" authorityName="J.-P.Lebrun &amp; Stork" authorityYear="1991" box="[682,830,1845,1871]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forgiarinii">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFD7A072FFCE5F8D1" box="[682,830,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">B. forgiarinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the mostly tridentate leaf apex, the sterile bracts being tranformed into sharply acuminate spines, the (1–)2–4-flowered spikes and the bract indumentum of stalked glandular hairs. It is distinctive among most species of sect. 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDD0E6CFC790766FBE5F808" authorityName="T. Anderson" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Delile" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[937,1086,1916,1942]" class="Bryopsida" genus="Acanthodium" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFC790766FBE5F808" box="[937,1086,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Acanthodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having subequal dorsal and ventral sepals, a 3-lobed corolla limb and non-appendaged anterior pair of stamens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C80436E0FFDD0E6DFF6D07DEFE02FED7" blockId="2.[136,1452,1664,2087]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,329]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDD0E6CFF6D07DEFE5FF840" authorityName="Baldesi &amp; Vollesen" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,388,1988,2014]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eilensis">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFF6D07DEFE5FF840" box="[189,388,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Blepharis eilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDD0E6CFDC107DFFD78F841" authorityName="J.-P.Lebrun &amp; Stork" authorityYear="1991" box="[529,675,1989,2015]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forgiarinii">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFDC107DFFDF9F840" box="[529,546,1989,2014]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFDFF07DFFD78F841" box="[559,675,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">forgiarinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFD0707DFFD33F840" box="[727,744,1989,2014]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">B</emphasis>
. d 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFCD307DEFCB5F840" box="[771,878,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">iplodonta</emphasis>
, also both endemic to north-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="B0AC7670FFDD0E6CFAD007DEFA84F840" box="[1280,1375,1988,2014]" name="Somalia" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Somalia</collectingCountry>
. These three species share the following feature not found otherwise in sect. 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDD0E6CFC5707F2FBC7F79C" authorityName="T. Anderson" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Delile" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[903,1052,2024,2050]" class="Bryopsida" genus="Acanthodium" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDD0E6CFC5707F2FBC7F79C" box="[903,1052,2024,2050]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Acanthodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 3-lobed corolla limb (or with basal lobes much reduced) combined with the anterior filaments lacking a forward-directed appendage and the dorsal and ventral sepals appearing subequal. It is assumed that the presence of subequal dorsal and ventral sepals is a primitive character. The corolla in sect. 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDC0E6DFE0300D8FDB3FF42" authorityName="T. Anderson" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Delile" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[467,616,194,220]" class="Bryopsida" genus="Acanthodium" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFE0300D8FDB3FF42" box="[467,616,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">Acanthodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also typically 5-lobed limb and reduction to a 3-lobed limb is considered a derived condition. It is not clear if the absence of anther appendage in these species of sect. 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDC0E6DFB4000FCFAFEFE9E" authorityName="T. Anderson" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Delile" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[1168,1317,230,256]" class="Bryopsida" genus="Acanthodium" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFB4000FCFAFEFE9E" box="[1168,1317,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">Acanthodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is primitive or the result of a secondary loss, although the combination with an advanced charcter like the 3-lobed corolla limb would suggest a derived state.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9CC46668FFDC0E6DFF58055CFD0AFA1E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345956" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6345956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6345956/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" startId="3.[136,229,1350,1372]" targetBox="[340,1247,353,1325]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="C80436E0FFDC0E6DFF58055CFD0AFA1E" blockId="3.[136,1451,1350,1408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFF58055CFF26FAC5" bold="true" box="[136,253,1350,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDC0E6DFED3055CFE75FAC5" authorityName="Baldesi &amp; Vollesen" authorityYear="2022" box="[259,430,1350,1371]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eilensis">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFED3055CFE75FAC5" box="[259,430,1350,1371]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">Blepharis eilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFE6A055CFE3CFAC5" bold="true" box="[442,487,1350,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">A–B</emphasis>
leaves, 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFDE4055CFD9EFAC2" bold="true" box="[564,581,1350,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">C</emphasis>
lower sterile bract, 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFCD4055CFCCEFAC5" bold="true" box="[772,789,1350,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">D</emphasis>
upper sterile bract, 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFC03055CFC38FAC5" bold="true" box="[979,995,1350,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">E</emphasis>
detail of leaf showing the indumentum, 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFAB7055CFAAEFAC5" bold="true" box="[1383,1397,1350,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">F</emphasis>
close up of fertile bract, 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFEEB0570FE95FA1E" bold="true" box="[315,334,1386,1408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">G</emphasis>
lower fertile bract, 
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFDDC0570FDC4FAE1" bold="true" box="[524,543,1386,1407]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">H</emphasis>
upper ferile bract.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C80436E0FFDC0E6DFF6D05B4FAC3F9AA" blockId="3.[136,1451,1454,1589]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">
On the other hand the presence of stalked capitate glands on the bracts is considered to be an advanced stage. This 
<typeStatus id="17008842FFDC0E6DFF5805C9FF63FA73" box="[136,184,1491,1517]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">type</typeStatus>
of hairs is found in many species of sect. 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDC0E6DFD5C05C8FCC8FA72" authorityName="Obermeyer ex Vollesen" authorityYear="2000" box="[652,787,1490,1516]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Scorpioidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FACFEAF2FFDC0E6DFD5C05C8FCC8FA72" box="[652,787,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">Scorpioidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on floral leaves, bracts and sepals and in sect. 
<taxonomicName id="0FBB4D63FFDC0E6DFACC05C9FA52FA72" authorityName="Vollesen" authorityYear="2000" box="[1308,1417,1491,1516]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Inopinata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
